{
  "texts": [
    "Participants were instructed to respond as quickly and as accurately as possible and could respond while the number or mask were on the screen.",
    "Trial order was semi-randomized in that target trials were never presented consecutively.",
    "After completing practice trials, participants completed 384 critical trials with the same parameters as the practice trials.",
    "To measure sustained attention, frequency of two kinds of errors-commission errors (i.e., responses during a target trial) and omission errors (i.e., a lack of response during a non-target trial) were combined, with higher numbers reflecting lower levels of sustained attention.",
    "Inflammatory markersMarkers of peripheral inflammation were assessed using dried blood spot (DBS) samples."
  ]
}